definition: public/collectively owned/common/international (e.g. high seas, metric system, calendar)/make public/fair/just/Duke, highest of five orders of nobility 五等爵位[wu3 deng3 jue2 wei4]/honorable (gentlemen)/father-in-law/male (animal)

sentences.english: Adult males are able to mate at any time.
sentences.chinese: 成年的公犬在任何时候都可以交配。

sentences.english: Dogs are not to be penalized if shown with a summer coat.
sentences.chinese: 公犬不应为夏季被毛而遭到处罚。

sentences.english: The male, however showed plenty of prey drive as well as confidence in new situations.
sentences.chinese: 而这条公犬表现出强烈的猎性，以及新情境下的自信。

sentences.english: Neck and shoulders heavily coated, especially in dogs, giving mane-like appearance. Tail and britches densely coated and heavily feathered.
sentences.chinese: 颈部和肩部有更长更粗的毛，特别是显示在公犬身上。

sentences.english: Some male Borzois are aggressive with other male dogs.
sentences.chinese: 一些公猎狼会挑衅其他的公犬。

sentences.english: Dogs (males) are judged first, in their age classes.
sentences.chinese: 公犬首先根据各个年龄组别分别受到评判。

sentences.english: Males should also be tested for brucellosis.
sentences.chinese: 公犬也同样应当检测布鲁氏菌病。

sentences.english: Once of our young males could go 10 to 12 minutes.
sentences.chinese: 有一次我的年轻公犬持续训练了10到12分钟。

sentences.english: Neck and shoulders heavily coated, giving a mane-like appearance that is more pronounced in mature males.
sentences.chinese: 颈肩部带有厚被毛，成熟公犬因此越发显得阳刚。

sentences.english: Male dogs have a rigid hierarchy.
sentences.chinese: 公犬有一个刻板的等级制度。

sentences.english: Below is a close up photo of the head of a sable male with the distinguishing sable markings.
sentences.chinese: 下一张图片是有区别的貂色斑纹的公犬。

sentences.english: This is commonly referred to as a tricolor. The…
sentences.chinese: 下一张图片是有区别的貂色斑纹的公犬。
